parameters:
"This island has little food. It's not just the exiles, even
the islanders can't get a satisfying meal. Be careful not to
starve to death."
...Oh? Did you get yourself a fishing rod?
Yes! Kisanosuke-san made it for me.

In that case, you'll need bait. Here are some worms I caught
by the shore. Feel free to use them for fishing.
Wow! Really!? Thank you so much, Village Chief♪

...If we had a boat, we could catch more fish, but since
this island is a place of exile, no boats are allowed other
than the ferry. It's truly inconvenient.

Mayor, it's been a while. I'm truly grateful for your help
back then.

When I saw the ship set sail from the cape, my heart
honestly trembled. It's a relief that everyone made it back
to Edo.

It's all thanks to the ship you and your ancestors built,
Mayor. I just had to come back to Mujou Island to express my
gratitude. I'm truly thankful.

The one who made the most of the opportunity was you, with
your extraordinary initiative. It's wonderful that you
received a pardon and regained your freedom. I want you to
enjoy the feeling of being able to go anywhere, on behalf of
my ancestors as well. Just make sure not to get caught
again.
Yes! Mayor, please live a long life as well.

The ship was wrecked along the way, and after fighting and
defeating a giant octopus, you managed to control it and
reach Uraga...? Hahahaha. That sure was a thrilling voyage.
Anyway, it's good that you were able to return to Edo
safely.
